+# Avoid these known failure modes (learned from past runs):
+- Default-DENY on allowlists. A fail-OPEN allowlist (permit on lookup miss) is a security bug - close it fail-closed, like the novel-instrument minting fix.
+- Two agents editing the same files corrupt each other. Stay within your task's file scope; shared interfaces belong in the 'contracts' task.
+- Never commit secrets. If gitleaks flags one: rotate it, purge history, gitignore, re-run.
+- run the prod build locally and fix all type/build errors before finishing
+- agent investigated but changed nothing; re-scope task
